CatDescriptText: Mr. Florice Johnson, 526 Oakwood Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 25, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that business and employment are as good as the Eisenhower administration declares that it is?" answer reads: "No, well simply because I've seen more people who are on relief and need help and are out of work, than there was under the Truman administration. In no way can I compare the Eisenhower administration with that under President Truman."
